        </w:rPr>
        <w:t>Executive Summary</w:t>
      </w:r>
    </w:p>
    <w:p w14:paraId="5983620B" w14:textId="20551531" w:rsidR="008631FA" w:rsidRPr="008631FA" w:rsidRDefault="00000000">
      <w:pPr>
        <w:rPr>
          <w:rFonts w:cstheme="minorHAnsi"></w:rFonts>
          <w:sz w:val="22"></w:sz>
          <w:szCs w:val="22"></w:szCs>
        </w:rPr>
      </w:pPr>
      <w:r w:rsidRPr="008631FA">
        <w:rPr>
          <w:rFonts w:cstheme="minorHAnsi"></w:rFonts>
          <w:sz w:val="22"></w:sz>
          <w:szCs w:val="22"></w:szCs>
        </w:rPr>
        <w:t>Management recommends proceeding with a regional launch in Q3. The current plan assumes a phased retail rollout, targeted category promotion, and disciplined working-capital management during the first two quarters after launch.</w:t>
      </w:r>
    </w:p>
    <w:p w14:paraId="225BBE35" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="007A523E" w:rsidRDefault="00000000">
      <w:pPr>
        <w:rPr>
          <w:rFonts w:cstheme="minorHAnsi"></w:rFonts>
          <w:sz w:val="22"></w:sz>
          <w:szCs w:val="22"></w:szCs>
        </w:rPr>
      </w:pPr>
      <w:r w:rsidRPr="008631FA">
        <w:rPr>
          <w:rFonts w:cstheme="minorHAnsi"></w:rFonts>
          <w:sz w:val="22"></w:sz>
          <w:szCs w:val="22"></w:szCs>
        </w:rPr>
        <w:t>The operating plan remains contingent on margin discipline, retailer onboarding quality, and a measured release cadence across priority markets. Leadership requested that the board packet preserve all active assumptions while clearly separating them from archived planning language.</w:t>
      </w:r>
    </w:p>
    <w:p w14:paraId="22D1E516" w14:textId="77777777" w:rsidR="002841A7" w:rsidRDefault="002841A7" w:rsidP="002841A7">
      <w:pPr>
        <w:rPr>
          <w:rFonts w:cstheme="minorHAnsi"></w:rFonts>
          <w:sz w:val="22"></w:sz>
          <w:szCs w:val="22"></w:szCs>
        </w:rPr>
      </w:pPr>
      <w:r w:rsidRPr="002841A7">
        <w:rPr>
          <w:rFonts w:cstheme="minorHAnsi"></w:rFonts>
          <w:sz w:val="22"></w:sz>
          <w:szCs w:val="22"></w:szCs>
        </w:rPr>
        <w:t xml:space="preserve">Management also reviewed execution risk by market, with particular emphasis on retailer onboarding timelines, promotional timing, and the operational burden of maintaining in-stock performance during the first eight weeks of launch. The current recommendation assumes that category resets will be phased in a way that limits avoidable working-capital pressure while preserving service levels for priority accounts.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        </w:t>
      </w:r>
    </w:p>
    <w:p w14:paraId="4C552EAD" w14:textId="29E96AAE" w:rsidR="008631FA" w:rsidRPr="008631FA" w:rsidRDefault="002841A7" w:rsidP="002841A7">
      <w:pPr>
        <w:rPr>
          <w:rFonts w:cstheme="minorHAnsi"></w:rFonts>
          <w:sz w:val="22"></w:sz>
          <w:szCs w:val="22"></w:szCs>
        </w:rPr>
      </w:pPr>
      <w:r w:rsidRPr="002841A7">
        <w:rPr>
          <w:rFonts w:cstheme="minorHAnsi"></w:rFonts>
          <w:sz w:val="22"></w:sz>
          <w:szCs w:val="22"></w:szCs>
        </w:rPr>
        <w:t xml:space="preserve">The team further noted that pricing discipline will be important during the introductory period. Temporary trade support may be used selectively, but the base case does not assume sustained discounting beyond the initial launch window. This approach is intended to protect margin integrity while still allowing the company to test velocity, repeat purchase behavior, and store-level execution quality.     </w:t>
      </w:r>
    </w:p>
